## Packages Folder

Shared packages in `packages/`:

```
packages/
├── README.md                    # Explains structure (committed)
├── @wegoby/types/               # Shared TypeScript types
├── @wegoby/ui/                  # UI component library
├── @wegoby/sensetree/           # Sensetree client SDK
├── @wegoby/percepta/            # Percepta client SDK
└── @wegoby/utils/               # Shared utilities
```

## Project-Specific Rules

Each project can have its own `.cursor/rules/`:

```
projects/{name}/.cursor/rules/
├── project.mdc          # Project-specific context
└── local.mdc            # Local conventions
```

These rules:
- Override or extend meta layer rules
- Contain project-specific patterns
- Are committed to the project repo

## Creating a New Project

1. Create folder in `projects/{name}/`
2. Initialize git: `git init`
3. Create basic structure
4. Add `.cursor/rules/project.mdc`
5. Link to meta layer packages

## Project Independence

Each project:
- Has its own git repository
- Has its own package.json
- Can be deployed independently
- Follows meta layer conventions
- Can have local rule overrides

